This paper is about adversarial training of deep neural networks, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields of computer science. However, given the focus on learning robust classifiers, it is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of efficient training techniques, which could also place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with the security of deep learning models, which could make it relevant to the sub-field of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
